I think you&#39;d want to use the [terms aggregation][1]. This will group by similar terms and return a count of each term. Look at the linked url for example.

In you case, it would look like this:

    GET /wfcharges/_search
    {
        &quot;aggs&quot; : {
            &quot;countfield&quot; : {
                &quot;terms&quot; : { &quot;field&quot; : &quot;mainid&quot; }
            }
        }
    }


  [1]: https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/search-aggregations-bucket-terms-aggregation.html

This query is going to be exactly what you need:
```js
GET /wfcharges/_search
{
  &quot;aggs&quot;: {
    &quot;countfield&quot;: {
      &quot;terms&quot;: {
        &quot;field&quot;: &quot;mainid&quot;,
        &quot;min_doc_count&quot;: 2
      }
    }
  }
}
```

It&#39;s going to aggregate by `mainid` field and tell that minimum document count for this bucket has to be 2 ( more than 1):

